                                <ul class="list-unstyled">
                                    <li class="ms-2 me-2">
                                        <i class="fas fa-circle me-2"></i>Panama Data Protection Law (Law 81 of March 26, 2019): Regulates personal data collection, processing, and storage, ensuring the protection of users’ rights within Panamanian jurisdiction.
                                    </li>
                                    <li class="ms-2 me-2">
                                        <i class="fas fa-circle me-2"></i>General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) principles: Upholds core principles like data minimization, lawful processing, and user consent for European Union data subjects.
                                    </li>
                                    <li class="ms-2 me-2">
                                        <i class="fas fa-circle me-2"></i>Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) Privacy Framework: Provides guidelines for ensuring privacy and data protection in the Asia-Pacific region.
                                    </li>
                                    <li class="ms-2 me-2">
                                        <i class="fas fa-circle me-2"></i>Organization of American States (OAS) Privacy Principles: Establishes shared privacy guidelines for member states to promote consistency in data handling.
                                    </li>
                                    <li class="ms-2 me-2">
                                        <i class="fas fa-circle me-2"></i>International humanitarian data protection standards: Ensures compliance with ethical data usage and protection in humanitarian operations, respecting the sensitivity of such information.
